article.description: — Javion Hamlet had 15 points, nine rebounds and seven assists as North Texas beat Old Dominion 61-55 in the quarterfinals of the Conference USA Tournament on Thursday night.
article.headline: Hamlet carries N. Texas over ODU 61-55 in CUSA tourney
article.linkText: Hamlet carries N. Texas over ODU 61-55 in CUSA tourney
article.story: FRISCO, Texas -- — Javion Hamlet had 15 points, nine rebounds and seven assists as North Texas beat Old Dominion 61-55 in the quarterfinals of the Conference USA Tournament on Thursday night. The Mean Green play Louisiana Tech in the semifinals Saturday. Mardrez McBride had 14 points for North Texas (15-9). Zachary Simmons added 13 points and seven rebounds. James Reese had six rebounds. Malik Curry had 17 points for the Monarchs (15-8). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
